Successfully analyzed the comic library application architecture. Here's what was found:

FRONTEND COMPONENTS (Svelte):
===========================

1. SIDEBAR & NAVIGATION
   - Sidebar.svelte: Generic mobile-responsive container
   - LibraryTree.svelte: Hierarchical folder browser with expand/collapse
   - TreeNode.svelte: Recursive tree node rendering
   - Navbar.svelte: Top navigation with search and theme toggle

2. COMIC DISPLAY
   - ComicCard.svelte: Grid/list variant card component
   - Supports progress indicators, folder badges, lazy loading

3. READER COMPONENTS
   - PageViewer.svelte: Comic page display
   - ReaderControls.svelte: Navigation controls
   - ReaderMenu.svelte: Overlay menu system
   - ReaderSettings.svelte: Reader preferences

4. ROUTING & PAGES
   - Home page: Libraries sidebar + continue reading + recent series
   - Browse: Browse all series in a library
   - Comic detail & reader: Full comic viewing
   - Series view: All volumes in a series
   - Search, favorites, continue-reading pages

BACKEND API (FastAPI):
=====================

All endpoints use /v2 base path

KEY ENDPOINTS:
- GET /libraries: All libraries with counts
- GET /library/{id}/info: Library details
- GET /library/{id}/folder/{folderId}: Browse folder contents
- GET /library/{id}/tree: Hierarchical folder tree (nested)
- GET /library/{id}/series: All series grouped with metadata
- GET /library/{id}/series/{name}: Comics in series
- GET /library/{id}/reading: Continue reading list
- GET /library/{id}/comic/{id}/fullinfo: Full comic info
- POST /library/{id}/comic/{id}/update: Update reading progress
- GET /library/{id}/cover/{hash}.jpg: Cover images

DATA ORGANIZATION:
==================

LIBRARIES: Top-level collections (e.g., "My Comics")

FOLDERS: Hierarchical file organization
- Tree structure with parent_id relationships
- Each folder contains comics and child folders
- Root folder marked with "__ROOT__" name (hidden)

SERIES: Comics grouped by name
- Uses metadata series field (priority 1)
- Falls back to normalized folder name (priority 2)
- Falls back to normalized filename (priority 3)
- Normalization removes: extensions, volume numbers, years, metadata tags
- Example: "Preacher (2019) (Digital)" → "Preacher"

COMICS: Individual comic files
- Stores: id, filename, path, hash, num_pages, reading progress
- Has metadata: series, volume, issue_number, publisher
- Reading progress: per-user current_page, is_completed, progress_percent

STATE MANAGEMENT:
=================

FRONTEND STORES:
- librariesStore: List of all libraries
- currentLibrary: Currently selected library
- themeStore: Dark/light theme preference
- readerStore: Reader state (current page, settings)

TREE STATE:
- expandedNodes: Set of expanded node IDs
- Persisted to localStorage by libraryId
- activeNodeId: Currently selected node

EVENTS:
- LibraryTree dispatches 'filter' events with folderId and folderName
- Parent components listen to filter events to update displayed comics

